The paper discusses the development of robust dynamical systems and networks, which involves modeling, analysis, and design of complex systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also focuses on autonomous aircraft systems and trajectory planning, which are related to robotics and control, indicating that cs.RO (Robotics) could be another likely sub-category. The use of methodology and tools for uncertainty quantification and robust design suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper mentions examples of application to energy usage in buildings and stability assessment of interconnected power networks, which are related to data analysis and optimization, indicating that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could be another possible sub-category.
